sentences: Quentin H. Poole (born 1957) is an English oboist, conductor and former boy chorister, who served as Head Chorister of King's College, Cambridge.
He was Director of Music of the Purcell School from 2001, from which he was made redundant in 2013.

He was made a Fellow of the Royal Academy of Music in 2004.
He appeared as a castaway on the BBC Radio programme Desert Island Discs on 26 December 1970.
